5:
Even in this distant land of Palpebra,
far from the sacred lands, we must
endeavor to walk in the path of the
Stars, and heed their teachings.
7:
O Stars, bless all your children, no
matter where they be. Come, let us
say a prayer together.
10:
All hail Lady Orvelle! You bring honor
to our faith!
15:
Lady Orvelle. Here are the requisite
documents for the day.
17:
As usual, if you would be so kind as
to provide your signature on each
one, we would be grateful. Blessings
upon you.
20:
Gah. More cooking the books... Every
form here is falsified in some way! I
suppose they'll be begging the
merchant's guild for donations
again soon.
22:
Day in, day out, it's always the exact
same thing! I've had it up to HERE
with this...
28: Grr! I can't take this anymore.
30:
Why am I stuck with all of this
meaningless busy work? I just want
to spend a day doing NOTHING for
once...
38:
Ah, that's more like it. There's nothing
like a day on the town, eating
spit-roasted skewers!
40:
Why, it's terribly unhealthy for a
young maiden like me to stay
cooped up in a church all day! I
need to slack off—or rather, take a
breather!
45:
Excuse me, could I have one churro
please?
55:
Man, it'd be a shame to have to
spend a lovely day like this plowing
through the Kaleidoscope. I'm glad
we went for a walk!
58:
I agree completely. Let's stop by the
guild and see if there are any
outdoor requests today—
75:
Wh-what was that just now? Some
sort of attack?
78:
Alk, take care. It looks like there
might be someone else collapsed
over there as well.
87:
Ngh... Ahhh... *yawn*
What is it? Way to interrupt me
during my hard-earned full-day
nap!
90:
Oh dear... What were these
scoundrels up to while I slept?
Perhaps I should refrain from
napping outside of Palpebra in the
future...
94:
Do you have any idea what could
have happened here?
99:
Ah, there's no need to worry. They're
merely unconscious from having
divine punishment inflicted upon
them.
108:
That's right. I prayed that whenever
someone approaches me with
malice in their heart, the Stars would
strike them down.
114:
Keep looking! You know how quickly
she tires, she can't have gone far!
122:
Please, I am being pursued and am
in need of help. Would you be willing
to grant me shelter?
126:
Huh? Who would want to go after
you?
129: Of course we will help you. Let's go.
139:
This is Starview Village, a place at
the intersection of many worlds.
144:
Starview? Many different worlds?!
How is this possible, I've never even
heard of this...
149:
Were we... teleported? Is this
perhaps... as it was written in the
secret scriptures...
*mumble* But if... Farl... modern
history... fabricated...
161:
A-anyway. Your pursuers will not be
able to make their way here. You're
safe for now.
164:
Could you maybe give us an
explanation about that? Why were
you being chased?
170:
My apologies for failing to elaborate
sooner. My name is Orvelle Libra.
172:
My pursuers are from the order of
holy knights. They were searching
for me, as I... am conspicuously
absent from my post at the
cathedral.
175:
Absent...? Holy knights?! Wait a
minute!
178:
I am a priestess of the Farlan faith.
I'm the current head of the
Palpebran parish. Though my office
is purely a symbolic one...
184:
You mean to tell me you're a
priestess?! At your age?!
188:
Well, technically speaking, I've
actually been officially canonized as
a saint!
193:
You're a literal SAINT? What are you
doing away from the church?
199:
I just... I got sick of working there! I
just wanted to spend ONE day doing
absolutely nothing, you know?
202: Are you sure you're actually a saint?!
205:
I suppose this means we've now
involved ourselves in your
unscheduled holiday...
210:
Don't worry, when it comes time to
work, I make sure to give it my all.
213:
The only work I skipped was all that
suspicious paperwork for
"donations" to the church.
216:
If anything, I was morally in the right
to do so!
220:
Anyway, forgetting all that! I was
wondering if it would be okay for me
to visit Starview Village again in the
future?
223:
Of course, I won't be divulging any
information about it to anyone. That
would only further complicate
things. What do you say?
227:
Of course, Miss Orvelle. We welcome
you.
230:
Really? Are we sure about that?
Doesn't that mean she has to play
hooky from the church again?
235:
That won't be a problem. I've done it
countless times before! So long as I
wait for the right opportunity to slip
out, I'll be fine.
237:
I'd love to explore this mysterious
town. It certainly beats rifling
through shady donation requests
and dealing with internal church
politics.
240:
I... see... Well, if that's what you think
is best, then I guess it's okay!
243:
Perhaps it would be best to have her
nearby for observation. That might
prevent any further... incidents.
247:
Hehe, thank you so much! I'll
definitely be coming by again soon!
